headline.main: HAVANA.; The Black Warrior at New-Orleans.

docs.lead_paragraph: By the arrival of the Black Warrior at New-Orleans. we have dates from Havana to the 3d inst., four days later. The Picayune received fall files of the Havana papers to the second inst. All Saint's Day and All Souls' Day were celebrated in Havana with and the solemnity observed here on the former day.

docs.lead_paragraph: The mail steamer Asia, from Liverpool on the 30th ult., arrived yesterday. Her news is of interest. In regard to Atlantic steam navigation, both the Government and Mr. CUNARD had declined to faver the linerich proposition. the former is, how ever, lending itself ernestly to the interests of the Galway line. The political topic of eminent interest in England was the Sepaches of Mr. JOHN BRIGHT, delivered at Birmingham during a three days, vish there.

headline.main: News From Mr. Fortune, in China.

docs.lead_paragraph: SIR: I have the honor to send you by this mail a parcel containing three packets of seeds, which may prove worth cultivation in the United States. The largest packet is probably of most importance. It is a species of Brassica, which is cultivated largely in the province of Chekiang for its oil, which is expressed from the seeds.

headline.main: The Argyll Rooms in London--The Nuisance of Street-Walking.

docs.lead_paragraph: From the London Saturday Review. Public decency is in a difficulty, and it seems than the remedy is worse than the disease. We appear to be in that condition which the Roman historian has described as the vice of a falling State---we can neither endure our vices not their cures.
